@node history "History"

    This is probably the last version of Statty, unless there are bugs that
    need fixing or somebody persuades me to add support for another tosser.

    3.5 - Rewritten to use rmh.library as only Arexx support library.
          Dropped support for 2.x database files.
          Parsing of Foozle.areas is more robust now.
          MailManager duplicate area handling works properly now.
          Can read arguments from a config file again.
    3.4 - Added french catalog.
          Code cleanup (As usual :-)).
          Added latest versions of support libraries.
    3.3 - Now uses standard READARGS() arguments instead of a cfg file
          Added rexxdossupport.library to distribution
          Minor change to statty.cd
          Fixed problems with KEEPOLD switch.
          Code cleanup.
    3.2 - Foozle section wasn't working.
          Added KEEPOLD switch.   
    3.1 - Added CrashMail support.
          Made the 'counter' more accurate when parsing the logfile.
    3.0 - Major rewrite. Lots of bugfixes and new features.


@endnode
@node dbformat "Database format"

    Date of first database <days>.<minutes>.<ticks>
    |   
    |          Date of last database <days>.<minutes>.<ticks>
    |          |
    |          |             Area file datestamp <days><minutes><ticks>
    |          |             |
    |          |             |            Keep old areas cookie
    |          |             |            |
    6598.390.0 7482.501.2552 747212942523 1
    1303 "AMIGAHARD_R23.PUB" 1 2
    8 "AMIGABBS_R23.PNT" 1 3
    2329 "AMIGAPROG_R23.PUB" 5 9
    |    |                   | |
    |    |                   | Number of messages from you.
    |    |                   | 
    |    |                   Number of messages to you.
    |    | 
    |    Area tag or username.
    |
    Total number of messages in area.
    
    @{" Example database file " link examples/statty.db/main}

    Note: The database format has changed slighly since v3.4 but Statty
    will update the database file automatically.

@endnode
@node logspotxport "logspotxport.rexx"

    Spot export log script.

    This script adds an entry to your spot.log each time you export
    echomail:

    | 02-May-96 06:28:23  Export startet
    ! 02-May-96 06:28:23  Area 'PB_POINT' got 2 messages
    | 02-May-96 06:28:23  Export ended

    How to install: 
    Edit the config section of the script.

    log         : The path to your Spot.log
    area        : The path to your Spot.areas file

    Install the script as a packer for each node that you export mail to.
    Enter the system settings editor and change your packer settings from
    <packer> to rx <path to script> <packer>.

    Eg: If you place the script in rexx: and your packer is 'lha a' it would 
    be: rx rexx:logspotxport.rexx lha a

@endnode
